    <outline text="Angel Reese — Lower leg/ankle injury sustained falling under the basket late in a win over the Seattle Storm (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.cbssports.com/wnba/news/portland-fire-atlanta-dream-where-to-watch-angel-reese-injury/" description="Puts a third-straight All-Star selection and Dream's first year with Reese (acquired in an offseason trade from Chicago) at risk of interruption during a stretch where the team is trying to build momentum after a five-game losing streak"/>
    <outline text="Brionna Jones — Meniscus tear in the right knee suffered in late January while playing overseas for USK Prague; underwent knee surgery at Emory Hospital (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.cbsnews.com/atlanta/news/atlanta-dreams-brionna-jones-nearing-return-expected-back-with-team-next-week/" description="Four-time All-Star center has yet to play a game for the Dream this season, a significant frontcourt loss to start the year"/>
    <outline text="Leonie Fiebich — Left foot soreness (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/final-injury-report-liberty-mystics-150000047.html" description="Liberty forward sidelined for consecutive games amid a compressed schedule that includes a quick turnaround for a game in Toronto"/>
    <outline text="Ezi Magbegor — Facial fracture (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/storm/ezi-magbegor-to-miss-seattle-storms-game-vs-washington-mystics-with-face-injury/" description="Storm without their starting center/forward for at least the near term"/>
    <outline text="Collin Murray-Boyles — Sprained thumb/finger, diagnosed after exiting a Summer League game against the Lakers (2026-07-10)" type="link" url="https://raptorsrepublic.com/2026/07/10/collin-murray-boyles-alijah-martin-to-miss-raptors-summer-league-opener/" description="Raptors lose their 2025 first-round pick (9th overall) for early Summer League reps as a point-forward, part of his developmental push"/>
    <outline text="Aliyah Boston — Lower right leg injury (2026-07-08)" type="link" url="https://athlonsports.com/wnba/indiana-fever/indiana-fever-announce-aliyah-boston-injury-update-la-sparks-game" description="Fever forced to manage the availability of both Boston and Caitlin Clark during a back-to-back stretch; Boston, a voted-in 2026 All-Star starter, is having a career-best scoring season (17.1 ppg on 50.4% shooting) and was in danger of missing her first game since May 17"/>
    <outline text="Jalen Brunson — Surgery to repair a left wrist injury that he played through during the Knicks' championship playoff run (2026-07-07)" type="link" url="https://sports.yahoo.com/nba/breaking-news/article/knicks-superstar-jalen-brunson-undergoes-left-wrist-surgery-expected-to-be-ready-for-2026-27-nba-season-155927234.html" description="Reigning Finals MVP and starting point guard sidelined for part of the offseason program, though expected back for training camp"/>
    <outline text="Skylar Diggins — Right knee injury; Diggins has said a knee surgery from last October has contributed to ongoing strain (2026-07-07)" type="link" url="https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/skys-skylar-diggins-ruled-vs-010259203.html" description="Comes as Diggins was moved to the bench for the first time in a decade, ending a streak of 341 consecutive starts; Sky beat Phoenix 77-66 in her absence"/>
    <outline text="A'ja Wilson — Foot injury sustained in a game against the Chicago Sky (2026-07-06)" type="link" url="https://www.nwaonline.com/news/2026/jul/07/injuries-taking-toll-throughout-wnba/" description="Aces without their All-Star forward/center for a short stretch, including a loss to Indiana"/>
    <outline text="Caitlin Clark — Aggravated back injury (2026-07-06)" type="link" url="https://www.nwaonline.com/news/2026/jul/07/injuries-taking-toll-throughout-wnba/" description="Fever have played without their All-Star starting guard for an extended stretch"/>
    <outline text="Napheesa Collier — Offseason surgery on both ankles (2026-07-06)" type="link" url="https://www.nwaonline.com/news/2026/jul/07/injuries-taking-toll-throughout-wnba/" description="Lynx have been without their All-Star forward for the entire season to date"/>
    <outline text="Olivia Miles — Calf strain suffered during a July 3 game vs. the New York Liberty, possibly linked to in-game cramping (2026-07-05)" type="link" url="https://www.espn.com/wnba/story/_/id/49287945/olivia-miles-sidelined-monday-sun-calf-injury" description="Costly absence for a Lynx team leaning on its rookie floor general; came a day after Miles was named a starter for the 2026 WNBA All-Star Game and while she remains a near-lock for Rookie of the Year (18.5 ppg, 4.8 rpg, 5.7 apg)"/>
    <outline text="Brandon Ingram — Recovering from offseason surgery (lower body) (2026-07-01)" type="link" url="https://bleacherreport.com/articles/25426220-brandon-ingram-injury-update-provided-raptors-after-surgery-latest-timeline-2026-nba-season" description="Raptors plan around his absence through the offseason program"/>
    <outline text="Josh Giddey — Arthroscopic surgery on right ankle (2026-07-01)" type="link" url="https://bleacherreport.com/articles/25427505-josh-giddey-injury-update-provided-bulls-after-ankle-surgery-latest-timeline-2026-nba-season" description="Bulls lose a starting guard for the entire offseason program"/>
    <outline text="JuJu Watkins — Recovering from a torn ACL that cost her the entire 2025-26 season (2026-07-01)" type="link" url="https://www.foxsports.com/stories/college-basketball/college-basketball-2026-2027-buzz-news-injuries-transfers" description="USC gets back its star guard after a full season lost to the injury"/>
    <outline text="Donnie Freeman — Torn right Achilles tendon, a non-contact injury suffered during a summer workout; underwent successful surgery performed by Dr. Martin O'Malley (2026-07-01)" type="link" url="https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/colleges/2026/07/01/st-johns-donnie-freeman-achilles-injury-pitino/81e54c60-75c4-11f1-b665-5f8be87f3787_story.html" description="Major setback for coach Rick Pitino and St. John's, who added the rising junior forward as a transfer-portal pickup this offseason; Freeman averaged 16.5 points and 7.2 rebounds last season at Syracuse"/>
    <outline text="Jaren Jackson Jr. — Turf toe surgery (right foot) (2026-06-30)" type="link" url="https://www.nba.com/news/memphis-grizzlies-jaren-jackson-jr-turf-toe-surgery" description="Grizzlies lose their All-Star big man through the offseason and possibly into training camp"/>
    <outline text="Kelsey Plum — Lower leg injury (2026-06-27)" type="link" url="https://bleacherreport.com/articles/25452286-angel-reese-kelsey-plum-headline-2026-wnba-all-star-game-reserves-full-roster-announced" description="Sparks lose a starting guard through their All-Star break stretch"/>
    <outline text="Bradley Beal — Hip fracture requiring season-ending surgery (2026-06-25)" type="link" url="https://www.nba.com/news/clippers-bradley-beal-out-season-hip-fracture" description="Clippers lose a veteran guard for the balance of the season and into next year's planning"/>
  </outline>
